---

## Quality Standards

### Spec must have:
- [ ] User stories with priorities (P1/P2/P3)
- [ ] Mermaid flowchart for EVERY user story
- [ ] Acceptance Criteria (AC-001, ...)
- [ ] Functional Requirements (FR-001, ...)
- [ ] Key Entities, Edge Cases, Success Criteria

### Plan must have:
- [ ] Technical Context table (stack-aware)
- [ ] Constitution Check gates
- [ ] Mermaid sequence diagrams (if API calls exist)
- [ ] Mermaid state diagrams (if entities have states)
- [ ] Mermaid ER diagrams (if new tables created)
- [ ] File-by-file implementation steps
- [ ] Testing strategy table

### Implementation must have:
- [ ] implementation.md with all FR/AC mapped to `@spec` anchors
- [ ] All tests passing
- [ ] changelog.md updated
- [ ] Visual baselines captured (if UI feature)

---

## Do Not

- вќЊ Write code without a spec
- вќЊ Leave specs stale after behavior changes
- вќЊ Skip updating `implementation.md`
- вќЊ Skip updating `changelog.md`
- вќЊ Create a spec without Mermaid flowcharts
- вќЊ Create a plan without diagrams for API/stateful/data features
- вќЊ Make silent architectural decisions вЂ” document them as ADRs

